      "description": "Offering an exceptional 1994 Mazda RX-7 FD, featuring the iconic 13B-REW rotary engine with its sequential Hitachi twin-turbocharger system performing flawlessly. This specimen maintains perfect 50/50 weight distribution and features a Torsen limited-slip differential for superior power delivery. The cooling system has been proactively upgraded with a high-capacity aluminum radiator to optimize thermal management, and all vacuum lines have been refreshed with high-temp Viton. The chassis is laser-straight with factory-spec double-wishbone suspension and zero bushing deflection. Compression test results are optimal and consistent across all rotor faces. A true survivor with immaculate paint depth and a pristine interior, representing the pinnacle of 90s JDM engineering.",
